\par
The \b \i window has border \i0 \b0 element determines, whether a frame will be displayed around a window or an element, selected by the {\uldb element identification number}{\v 20593}. The \b \i window has caption \i0 \b0 element determines, whether a caption will be displayed on the window upper border. For dialog elements a thickened inner frame will be used instead of the caption. If the window's or element's caption is on, but their frame is off, a thin frame will be used.\par
\par
\{bmc IDF20749.bmp\} \tab \b \i always on top \i0 \b0 \par
\par
