The \b \i create... \i0 \b0 program elements create a dialog element the visibility of which is switched off, return the {\uldb element identification number}{\v 20593} and set it as a selected element for the subsequent operations.\par
\par
The {\uldb text}{\v 20600} program element sets or returns the text of selected entry of the listbox, text of the list's editing field, or text of the table cell. Current row of the listbox or table can be selected by the {\uldb actual position}{\v 20777} element. A cell on the table row can be selected by the {\uldb actual position 2}{\v 20941} element.\par
\par
The \b \i create tabs \i0 \b0 element creates tabs dialog element. Single tabs can be added or deleted similarly as listbox entries. Selected tab can be found out or adjusted with the {\uldb actual position}{\v 20777} element and according to the number of selected tab update content of the window (create or delete appropriate dialog elements in the window).\par 
\par
As parameter of the \b \i create table \i0 \b0 element a multiline text list defining table columns can be entered. Texts of individual rows are used as titles of the table head. If all rows of the list are empty then the table will have no head. Width of the selected table column can be set or found out by the \b \i width of table column \i0 \b0 element. Column selection is done by the {\uldb actual position 2}{\v 20941} element. If a valid table column is selected (its value is not -1) when changing selected row by the {\uldb actual position}{\v 20777} element then position of the table cursor is updated, too. By the \b \i align of table column \i0 \b0 element align of the table column can be changed: 0=left (default), 1=right, 2=center. This proves also in the table head except column 0, head of which is always aligned to the left.\par
